fields.description:
1. Responses homogeneity DONE!
Due to accomplish the homogeneity of the api responses, some of the object retorned have distinct json atributes.
See the next objects:

DONE! AchievementResponse.id 
DONE! AchievementResponse.appId
DONE! AchievementResponse. type should be an ENUM!
DONE! PlayerAchievementDataResponse.applicationId
DONE! PlayerAchievementDataResponse.achievementId

2. @Value convention DONE!

GamificationConfiguration recover the env value by Env.getProperty.
Change it to recover by @Value annotattion

3. Mongo configuration recover properties (NOT APPLICABLE!)

MongoConfiguration must recover the properties by a @Bean object in the GamificationConfiguration.

4. MaxAchievementValueReachedException avoid exception bussines logical programing...!!!!!
It's discouraged, breaks SOLID and GRASP patterns DONE!

5. Use a external bean GamificacionProperties. Avoid use @Value outside configuration package for future further operations DONE!

6. The names of the methods are ambiguous. In the service the methods must be have a names that represents the business logic. Player Achievement Service DONE!

7. Comparations at AchievementServiceDefault DONE!

Left compare asigment:
change this --> if(achievement.getVisibility().equals(VISIBILITY.Public.toString())) {
to -->
if(VISIBILITY.Public.equals(achievement.getVisibility())) {

Use collections to return a list instead of add external list.
List<AchievementResponse> result =
achievements.stream().forEach(a -> {
})..collect(Collectors.toList());

8. AchievementRequestValidator DONE!

if(achievementRequest.getType()!=null){
	    	if(achievementRequest.getType().equals(TYPE.Binary)) {

Better:
TYPE.Binary.equals(achievementRequest.getType())

This way avoid nulls and concatenated <if>

9. Review RestController, some controller returns bad http code

10. When making a request to get an achievement to operation "/api/1/achievements/{id}" of API "achievement-controller" the object returned have the achievementId to null (DONE!)

11.  Business model and Repository are mixed into package model.achievement.

fields.description:
As a brazilian developer I want to use the MessageBroker in Brazil. So that I will be able to send sms message or push to brazilian mobile phones. 

This requires to release a new instance of our service which will send SMS messages through brazilian CAM SMS infraestructure. 

We must do: 

- Release a new instance of Message broker
- Use brazilian CAM SMS infrastructure
- Put API manager in front of our service


Acceptance criteria 
------------------------

- Brazil should be able to make requests to our service 
- Brazil should be able to send a SMS with message broker
- Brazil should be able to send a Push with message broker

} 
This registration works ok.
{
  "applicationId": "181",
  "deviceId": "deviceid-000001",
  "registerId": "this-is-the-register-id-generated-by-provider02"
} 
This registration doesn´t and must work.
